declare SFilterDF "Second-order direct-form digital filter, specified by ANALOG transfer-function polynomials B(s)/A(s), and a frequency-scaling parameter.  Digitization via the bilinear transform is built in.

USAGE:
tf2s(b2,b1,b0,a1,a0,w1), where 

         b2 s^2 + b1 s + b0
H(s) = --------------------
           s^2 + a1 s + a0
**w1 = the desired digital frequency (in radians/second) corresponding to analog frequency 1 rad/sec (i.e., s = j).

METHOD: 
Bilinear transform scaled for exact mapping of w1.

REFERENCE: 
https://ccrma.stanford.edu/~jos/pasp/Bilinear_Transformation.html";

//////////////////////
declare FFilterDF  "First-order direct-form digital filter, specified by ANALOG transfer-function polynomials B(s)/A(s), and a frequency-scaling parameter.

USAGE: 
tf1s(b1,b0,a0,w1), where 

       b1 s + b0
H(s) = ----------
         s + a0

** w1 is the desired digital frequency (in radians/second) corresponding to analog frequency 1 rad/sec (i.e., s = j).

METHOD: 
Bilinear transform scaled for exact mapping of w1.

REFERENCE: 
https://ccrma.stanford.edu/~jos/pasp/Bilinear_Transformation.html";

